ğŸ§  Model Information
The classification model is a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) built using the Keras API within TensorFlow. 
To achieve high accuracy, it leverages Transfer Learning with the VGG16 architecture, pre-trained on the ImageNet dataset.
The model was then fine-tuned on the specific task of classifying brain tumor MRI scans.
